OL,6,F"Our net is tightening all the time as
OL,7,Fwe trawl through hundreds of hours of
OL,8,Ffootage and intelligence to find those
OL,9,Fwho have played any part in the
OL,10,Fregion's recent disorder.
OL,12,F"The behaviour demonstrated by these
OL,13,Fmen is certainly not welcome in our
OL,14,Fcommunities ` and we will continue to
OL,15,Fdo everything in our power to ensure
OL,16,Fthey are held accountable."
OL,18,FFourteen people have now been
OL,19,Fconvicted for their part in unrest in
OL,20,FSunderland - four of which have been
OL,21,Fjailed, as others await sentencing.
